Description: The Ark of the Covenant, which the Lord himself instructed Moses to construct (Exodus 25:8), is one of the most iconic symbols in biblical history. It demonstrates the fact that God Almighty, the maker of heaven and earth, chose to dwell among His chosen people. Our representation of the Ark of the Lord (Joshua 3:13) brings to life the beauty and symbolism of the original Ark, containing the gold jar of manna, Aaron’s staff, and the stone tablets of the covenant (Hebrews 9:4). The Ark heartens the believer with the confidence that we now have access into the presence of God, once reserved for the high priest alone, through the sacrifice of Yeshua (Hebrews 10:19). 3”h x 4.25”w x 2.25”d.

What relevance does it have for us that Jesus is Jewish and what difference should it make to our faith?
 
In The Jewish Jesus, David Hoffbrand explores the answers to these and related questions in a way that is accessible to everyone.

It’s time to discover the Jewish Jesus!

Name: The Megillah Scroll of Esther- Feast of Purim
Meta Description: Esther Holy Scripture Scroll
Description:
Esther Holy Scripture Scroll


 This strikingly beautiful Scripture Scroll of Esther is a reproduction of a Megillat Esther created by Moshe Ben Avraham in 1617 in Ferrara, Italy. The original scroll was inscribed on parchment with spectacular decorations in vivid color accompanying the text. The area between the columns of text is decorated brilliantly with flora and fauna motifs. At the top of each page appears the torso of a man in navy blue and red fez, bespeaking the culture of Persia where the story took place. Also at the top of each page is a painting of that page's scene with subtitles and accompanying text. The scenes in the scroll depict life—culture, clothing, interior design, and food— as the artist knew it at the beginning of the seventeenth century. The ornate round case stands 12” tall, and 4.25” in diameter.  Check it out on YOUTUBE https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=whz5OUv6G9U
Meta Keyword: Esther Holy Scripture Scroll

Name: Chamber of the Last Supper matted
Meta Description: Chamber of the Last Supper
Description:
Chamber of the Last Supper

Jerusalem, Israel-Circa 1900

Description

The Chamber of Last Supper Room is a second-story room in Jerusalem recognized as the "upper room" in which Jesus shared the Last Supper with the disciples. This image is a reminder of the life and death of Christ relived each time we celebrate the Eucharist, first given to us by Christ himself within the walls of this chamber.

This image captures the rising of majestic columns before they erupt into scrolls that envelope the entire space. It is considered the site where many other events described in the New Testament took place, including the descent of the Holy Spirit upon the disciples the day of Pentecost and the gathering of the disciples after the Ascension of Jesus.

And he took bread, gave thanks and broke it, and gave it to them, saying, “This is my body given for you; do this in remembrance of me.” Luke 22:19

Meta Description: Western Wall Temple Mount,
Description:
Garden of Gethsemane Jerusalem

Jerusalem, Israel-Circa 1900

Description

The holy site of Gethsemane is a garden at the foot of the Mount of Olives in Jerusalem. Christian tradition names this Holy Site as the place where Jesus prayed in agony before he was betrayed by Judas Iscariot and arrested by the Roman chort. Beside the garden is the Church of All Nations, built over the rock on which Jesus is believed to have prayed.

Still a Holy Site of pilgrimage today, this image reminds us of the humbling agony of Jesus’ sacrificial love for us, so that in our time of agony, we can reflect on the same humility..

My Father, if it is possible, may this cup be taken from me. Yet not as I will, but as you will." Mt 26:39

Name: Church of the Holy Sepulchre, Israel-Circa 1900  Matted
Meta Description: Western Wall Temple Mount,
Description:
Church of the Holy Sepulchre

Jerusalem, Israel-Circa 1900

Description

The Church of the Holy Sepulchre is located in the Old City of Jerusalem and considered the holiest Christian site in the world. It stands on a site between Golgotha and Calvary, believed to be where Jesus was crucified, and the tomb, or sepulchre, where he was buried.

The site remained buried until Emperor Constantine converted to Christianity and commissioned numerous churches to be built throughout the Holy Land. In the course of the excavations, Constantine's mother St. Helena, is said to have discovered the True Cross near the tomb. It is said she discovered three crosses - those of the two thieves and that of Christ. To discern the one belonging to Christ, a sick man was brought to touch to each one, and he was miraculously healed by one of them.

Constantine's builders dug away the hillside to leave the rock-hewn tomb of Christ isolated and with enough room to built a church around it.

At the place where Jesus was crucified, there was a garden, and in the garden a new tomb, in which no one had ever been laid. John 19:41

Name: Mount of Olives Jerusalem, Israel-Circa 1900 Matted
Meta Description: Mount of Olives
Description:
Mount of Olives

Jerusalem, Israel-Circa 1900

Description

The Mount of Olives is a ridge running along the east side of Jerusalem and to this day remains a pilgrimage site in the Holy Land. It was the location of many events in the Bible. The very location where David wept in defeat and where Jesus was betrayed and rejected, will be the place where Jesus returns in triumph over all His enemies.

Jesus made many visits to this location and after the trials, crucifixion, and resurrection, Jesus once again stood on the Mount of Olives. According to scripture, the prophet Zechariah declared that Jesus will return not only in the same way, but to the same place. This image is a symbol of faith in the return of Jesus..

.

The Lord will go forth and fight against those nations, as when He fights on a day of battle. On that day His feet will stand on the Mount.” Zechariah 14:3-4

Name: The River Jordan Israel-Circa 1900
Meta Description:
The River Jordan
Israel-Circa 1900
Description:
The River Jordan

Jerusalem, Israel-Circa 1900

Description

The spiritual significance of the Jordan River, which runs through the Holy Land, cannot be overstated. For both Judaism and Christianity, the Jordan plays a decisive role in Bible history. It was in the crossing of this river that the nation of Israel would finally enter the Promised Land, led by Joshua, the successor of Moses. A millennium later, the new Joshua, Jesus of Nazareth, would begin his public ministry after being baptized in the Jordan by John the Baptist. He would gain admittance for believers to the Promised Land of heaven.

This image of a solitary figure gazing at the Jordan captures the simplicity and yet beauty of the site. It invites us to travel back in time and to contemplate in reverence the baptism of Jesus or perhaps to thank Him for a healing or miracle He has brought into our lives..

“After me comes he who is mightier than I, ... and he will baptize you with the Holy Spirit.” Mark 1:7-8

Name: Wondrous Love
Meta Description: Wondrous Love
Description:
Jewish believer Joel Weiskopf has been a professional jazz musician who has played with jazz greats such as Woody Herman, Stan Getz, Gerry Mulligan, Jimmy Cobb and John Patitucci, among many others.
 
Joel Weiskopf Echad is a new Messianic-Gospel-Jazz group led by Jewish believer and Jazz pianist Joel Weiskopf. Top jazz vocalists and instrumentalists join Joel on his new recording Wondrous Love, which features worshipful gospel-jazz arrangements of traditional Jewish liturgical songs, hymns, contemporary Christian songs and originals. A new, refreshing way to enjoy some of your favorite worship songs and a great way to share the gospel of Yeshua with friends and relatives!

    20 years ago, when he was frustrated, burned out,  broken and hurt, he made the decision to trust Jesus with his life. Since then, God has done an awesome work of grace and healing in Joel's life. 
    This CD is the culmination of many years of prayer, and features many of Joel's original compositions and arrangements written for jazz ensemble and vocalists. 
    Joel has served as pianist at several churches and Messianic congregations in the New York City including The Brooklyn Tabernacle, Congregation Beit Hofesh and most recently, Congregation Shaar Adonai, and has also served at several Jews for Jesus ingatherings, as well as High Holy day services. 
    His desire is to meld the rich genres of Messianic, Gospel and Jazz music in a way that they can reach as many people as possible, both Jew and Gentile, with the life-changing message that Yeshua is indeed the Messiah!


Messianic recording artist Joel Weiskopf

Jericho, Israel-Circa 1900

Description

The story of Jericho inspires us all to follow God’s directive and to have faith and perseverance. The Israelites marched around the walls once every day for seven days with the seven priests. On the seventh day, they marched around the walls seven times. The priests blew their seven horns raising a great shout from the Israelites, and the walls of the city fell.

. In the face of insurmountable odds, victory over the enemy can sometimes come with something as simple as prayer, patience, and doing what God has asked of us.

It was by faith that the people of Israel marched around Jericho for seven days, and the walls came crashing down.” Heb 11:30

Name: Jacobs Well Sychar, Israel-Circa 1900
Meta Description:
Jacobs Well
Sychar, Israel-Circa 1900
Description:
Jacobs Well Sycharr

Israel-Circa 1900

Description

Jacob’s Well is located in the West Bank and is often considered the most authentic site in the Holy Land, since no one can move a well. It is the site where Jesus asked a Samaritan woman for a drink while He was resting after a tiring journey. In speaking with a Samaritan and, even more shocking, a woman, and asking her for a drink, He was breaking all cultural taboos. Because of her positive response, however, He introduced her to living waters and a new life in communion with Him.

In this world of sin and division, no holy site more explicitly represents the love and acceptance that Jesus asks us all to have toward one another, regardless of our beginnings or differences. He asks this of us and in return offers us “living waters”..

But whosoever drinketh of the water that I shall give him shall never thirst. John 4:14

Full of courage in the face of a giant with whom no other would contend, he easily slays him defeating the forces of evil that threatened his people. .

“You come against me with sword and spear and javelin, but I come against you in the name of the Lord Almighty” 1 Samuel 17:45

Name: Fishermen on the Lake Israel-Circa 1900
Meta Description:
Fishermen on the Lake 
Israel-Circa 1900
Description:
Fishermen on the Lake I

Israel-Circa 1900

Description

The Sea of Galilee was the site where Jesus called His first disciples. While walking beside the lake, he saw two brothers, Peter and his brother Andrew. They were casting a net into the lake. Going on from there, he saw two other brothers, James and his brother John. They were in a boat with their father Zebedee, preparing their nets. Jesus called them, and immediately they left their nets to follow him. .

The brilliant colors in this depiction of fishermen on the lake, gives pause to consider how great the call that these simple fishermen were moved to leave the beauty of their environment, livelihood and even their families, to follow the Son of Man. With courage from the Holy Spirit they left the comforts of life to pursue the truth. We all encounter at some point in our lives a calling to the truth that often requires we leave our space of comfort and predictability in favor of or faith in knowing we are dedicating our lives to truth and to lovingly and courageously bring others with us...

“And he saith unto them, “Follow me, and I will make you fishers of men.” Mt. 4:19

Name: Camp Gilgal WEST 2018 - Adventure Camp
Description: Adventure camp was designed with young adults in mind to be a part road trip, part camping adventure. This year we’re whitewater rafting on the Klamath River near the Oregon border, and it's an amazing amount of fun! We'll start at a ranch in Oroville (near Chico) and end in San Francisco. In between will be a road trip, rafting on a beautiful river, sleeping where you can see more stars than you can imagine, and on our drive back to San Francisco we’ll pass through the Avenue of the Giants (the coast redwoods). Adventure camp is designed to foster community among our campers and staff as we dig deeper into God’s Word together. Surrounded by the beauty of His creation, we seek to grow closer to the Lord and each other.

Name: Camp Gilgal WEST 2018 - Junior Camp
Description: You can search the world high and low, and you won’t be able to find as much fun as we pack into two weeks of junior camp! There’ll be swimming, horseback riding, Tabernacle (Bible teaching and worship), Hebrew (ranging from those who don't know the alphabet at all to those who can speak it), campfires, crafts, night games, theme meals, and some special surprises. This will be our 27th season! Nearly all our staff has grown up in our Camp Gilgal program, and we know how to make it fun for our campers. Our high staff to camper ratio provides a safe and nurturing environment for our precious campers. You don’t want to miss junior camp!
Short Description:
Silver Spur Christian Camp and Retreat Center
Tuolumne, California (near Sonora)

Name: Camp Gilgal WEST 2018 - Teen Camp
Description: Teen camp is an action-packed and fun-filled week! We hike in Yosemite National Park, study God’s word in Tabernacle (Bible lessons and worship), enjoy a mega slip-n-slide and adventure activities (rock wall climbing, ropes course and a giant swing), as well as paintball, swimming, night games, and much more. Campers grow in their faith in Yeshua, have opportunities to see how God has uniquely gifted them, and make friendships that will last a lifetime. Again, our high staff to camper ratio provides our campers a personal and engaging experience. Get ready for an epic week!
Short Description:
Camp Oakhurst
Coarsegold, California (near Yosemite National Park)

Name: Camp Gilgal MIDWEST 2018 - Junior Camp
Description: Get ready for junior camp 2017! There’s no better way to spend a summer than riding horses, swimming in the lake, and studying the Scriptures. During these fun-filled two weeks, campers will have a blast participating in activities such as rock climbing, archery, time at a rifle range, learning Hebrew (ranging from beginner to just beyond post-beginner), making a cool craft, gaga ball, boating, a petting zoo, and much, much more. Transportation is available from Chicago.

Name: Camp Gilgal MIDWEST 2018 - Teen Camp
Description: Teen camp at Cran-Hill Ranch will be an epic week of action and fun. Our days at the ranch will be filled with paintball, zip lining, horseback riding, rifle range shooting, tomahawk throwing, a ropes course and rock wall climbing, Jewish tradition, Bible studies and worship. During our free time we’ll be boating and swimming down at the lake or hanging out around the campfire. It's the perfect week to grow in your faith, establish deep friendships with other believers in Messiah, and make memories that last a lifetime!

Name: Camp Gilgal MIDWEST 2018 - Adventure Camp
Description: Adventure camp is an opportunity for older teens to spend time outside of their normal lives building strong friendships, growing personally through challenging activities, meeting the Lord through worship and Bible study, and having a blast together. Stay tuned for more details!

Name: Camp Gilgal EAST 2018 - Junior Camp
Description: Junior camp is two weeks long, giving our junior campers plenty of time to get adjusted to camp life, try out archery, work on their craft projects, spend time in the pool, and hang out around the campfire. Our campers will go horseback riding, learn Hebrew and grow closer to the Lord during Tabernacle (worship and Bible lessons). Junior camp is packed full of fun and opportunities for campers to take ownership of their faith in Yeshua and make friendships that last a lifetime. Transportation is available from Washington, D.C., New Jersey and New York City.
Short Description:
Camp Pinnacle
Voorheesville, New York (near Albany)

Name: Camp Gilgal EAST 2018 - Teen Camp
Description: Teen camp is eight days filled to the brim with crazy games, swimming, Tabernacle (age-specific Bible studies and worship), campfires, and a trip to the Adirondacks where we sleep in tents. Finally, to top it all off, we take a day to go whitewater rafting! Camp is tons of fun and is a great chance to get away, grow in your faith in Messiah and make some of the best friends you’ll ever have. Come with us this summer. Transportation is available from Washington, D.C., New Jersey and New York City.
Short Description:
Camp Pinnacle
Voorheesville, New York (near Albany)

Name: Camp Gilgal EAST 2018 - Adventure Camp
Description: Adventure camp is the best week of the year for high school students! Take on the challenge of adventure, fun, friends, and spiritual growth during a wilderness camping trip in Ohiopyle State Park of Western Pennsylvania. In between is a week-long trek where we camp out, cook our own meals, spend time with the Lord and each other in worship and studying His Word, and take advantage of the many activities the region offers. This part of Pennsylvania has everything from caves to awesome biking to hiking to incredible architecture (trust us!). The adventure begins and ends with a road trip from NYC.

Name: The Day Jesus Did Tikkun Olam by Rich Robinson
Meta Title: The Day Jesus Did Tikkun Olam
Meta Description: The Day Jesus Did Tikkun Olam
Description:
Description of The Day Jesus Did Tikkun Olam: Jewish Values and the New Testament 166 pages

Tikkun Olam is Hebrew for “repair of the world”—making the world a better place. For Jewish people, it’s an essential obligation alongside honor for parents, giving to charity and many more. In this treasure of a book, author Richard A. Robinson tours the reader through seven Jewish core values from the Old Testament, on through Jewish tradition, and then on into the New Testament. Through a rich assortment of anecdotes, timely illustrations and a dose of Jewish humor, Robinson shows how Jesus embodied these ethical values—and how the ultimate day He “repaired the world” was the day He died for our sins. Written with your Jewish friends and relatives in mind, this delightful volume will be sure to enhance your own understanding of the New Testament as well!
Short Description: The Day Jesus Did Tikkun Olam
Meta Keyword: The Day Jesus Did Tikkun Olam

Name: Camp Gilgal EAST 2019 - Adventure Camp
Description: Adventure camp is the best week of the year for high school students! Take on the challenge of adventure, fun, friends, and spiritual growth during a wilderness camping trip in Ohiopyle State Park of Western Pennsylvania. In between is a week-long trek where we camp out, cook our own meals, spend time with the Lord and each other in worship and studying His Word, and take advantage of the many activities the region offers. This part of Pennsylvania has everything from caves to awesome biking to hiking to incredible architecture (trust us!). The adventure begins and ends with a road trip from NYC.

Name: Camp Gilgal East 2019 - WWW
Description: WWW takes the excitement, adventure, friends, and fun of our Camp Gilgal summer programs and packs it all into one incredible weekend. We’ll go sledding, maybe play some GaGa ball and have an awesome time together. Whether reconnecting with camp friends from summers past or trying out Camp Gilgal for the first time, WWW is an opportunity to meet with God and with other Jewish believers. Don’t forget, at WWW there might even be snow! We hope that you’ll join us for Wonderful. Winter. Weekend. 2019!
Short Description: WWW takes the excitement, adventure, friends, and fun of our Camp Gilgal summer programs and packs it all into one incredible weekend. We’ll go sledding, maybe play some GaGa ball and have an awesome time together. Whether reconnecting with camp friends from summers past or trying out Camp Gilgal for the first time, WWW is an opportunity to meet with God and with other Jewish believers. Don’t forget, at WWW there might even be snow! We hope that you’ll join us for Wonderful. Winter. Weekend. 2019!

Name: Camp Gilgal EAST 2019 - Junior Camp
Description: Junior camp is two weeks long, giving our junior campers plenty of time to get adjusted to camp life, try out archery, work on their craft projects, spend time in the pool, and hang out around the campfire. Our campers will go horseback riding, learn Hebrew and grow closer to the Lord during Tabernacle (worship and Bible lessons). Junior camp is packed full of fun and opportunities for campers to take ownership of their faith in Yeshua and make friendships that last a lifetime. Transportation is available from Washington, D.C., New Jersey and New York City.
Short Description:
Camp Pinnacle
Voorheesville, New York (near Albany)

Name: Camp Gilgal EAST 2019 - Teen Camp
Description: Teen camp is eight days filled to the brim with crazy games, swimming, Tabernacle (age-specific Bible studies and worship), campfires, and a trip to the Adirondacks where we sleep in tents. Finally, to top it all off, we take a day to go whitewater rafting! Camp is tons of fun and is a great chance to get away, grow in your faith in Messiah and make some of the best friends you’ll ever have. Come with us this summer. Transportation is available from Washington, D.C., New Jersey and New York City.
Short Description:
Camp Pinnacle
Voorheesville, New York (near Albany)

Name: Camp Gilgal WEST 2019 - Wonderful Winter Weekend
Description: Camp Gilgal Wonderful Winter Weekends provide an opportunity for our campers to get together between summer camps, and our prospective campers to “test drive” Camp Gilgal. The weekends start with a Shabbat dinner on Friday evening and end with lunch on Sunday. In between is some major fun and spiritual encouragement. Because California is huge, we have two weekend camps: one in Southern California (Mile High Pines in Angelus Oaks) and one in Northern California (Dream Mountain Christian Camp in Murphys).
Short Description: Mile High Pines in Angelus Oaks

Name: Camp Gilgal WEST 2019- Junior Camp
Description: You can search the world high and low, and you won’t be able to find as much fun as we pack into two weeks of junior camp! There’ll be swimming, horseback riding, Tabernacle (Bible teaching and worship), Hebrew (ranging from those who don't know the alphabet at all to those who can speak it), campfires, crafts, night games, theme meals, and some special surprises. This will be our 27th season! Nearly all our staff has grown up in our Camp Gilgal program, and we know how to make it fun for our campers. Our high staff to camper ratio provides a safe and nurturing environment for our precious campers. You don’t want to miss junior camp!
Short Description:
Silver Spur Christian Camp and Retreat Center
Tuolumne, California (near Sonora)

Name: Camp Gilgal WEST 2019 - Teen Camp
Description: Teen camp is an action-packed and fun-filled week! We hike in Yosemite National Park, study God’s word in Tabernacle (Bible lessons and worship), enjoy a mega slip-n-slide and adventure activities (rock wall climbing, ropes course and a giant swing), as well as paintball, swimming, night games, and much more. Campers grow in their faith in Yeshua, have opportunities to see how God has uniquely gifted them, and make friendships that will last a lifetime. Again, our high staff to camper ratio provides our campers a personal and engaging experience. Get ready for an epic week!
Short Description:
Camp Oakhurst
Coarsegold, California (near Yosemite National Park)

Name: Camp Gilgal WEST 2019 - Adventure Camp
Description: Adventure camp was designed with young adults in mind to be a part road trip, part camping adventure. This year we’re whitewater rafting on the Klamath River near the Oregon border, and it's an amazing amount of fun! We'll start at a ranch in Oroville (near Chico) and end in San Francisco. In between will be a road trip, rafting on a beautiful river, sleeping where you can see more stars than you can imagine, and on our drive back to San Francisco we’ll pass through the Avenue of the Giants (the coast redwoods). Adventure camp is designed to foster community among our campers and staff as we dig deeper into God’s Word together. Surrounded by the beauty of His creation, we seek to grow closer to the Lord and each other.
